{"parse":{"title":"Future map (organizational planning)","pageid":14981627,"revid":805995329,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\nThe <b>future map</b> is a method for building scenarios based on the collection of anticipated events.\n</p><p>The concept is based on the idea that a group of people who integrate the partial visions of its members into a common, shared, discussed, large enough, collection of anticipated events it can eventually reveal its own \"shared future\".\n</p><p>Because the <a href=\"/wiki/Policy_Analysis_Market\" title=\"Policy Analysis Market\">FutureMap</a> methodology is dynamic and implemented on a <a href=\"/wiki/Wiki\" title=\"Wiki\">wiki</a>-platform the Future projected by the group is constantly under revision. By process, the community learns how to adapt to future changes and increases its ability to face \"unexpected events\", it improves what the author calls its <b>future-readiness</b>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Future_map_(organizational_planning)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Policy_Analysis_Market\" title=\"Policy Analysis Market\">Policy Analysis Market</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Information_Awareness_Office#Futures_Markets_Applied_to_Prediction_(FutureMAP)\" title=\"Information Awareness Office\">Information Awareness Office FutureMap Project</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Future_map_(organizational_planning)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Bill Sharpe and Kees Van Der Heijden 